# CSS TEST: NOT REAL CONTENT!

This article $x = 5$ explores the concept of *energy* in modern physics.
We also highlight **key equations** and experimental<sup><a id="fnref1" href="#fn1">1</a></sup> results.

?<aside class="footnote-block" data-fn-num="✱">
  For a detailed review, see <em>Smith et al. (2024)</em>. 
  The effect size was large across all subgroups.
</aside>


## Key properties

- Energy is conserved
- Energy can change forms
- Measured in joules (J)

